description: Backend coding standards — Express, MongoDB, JWT auth, error handling
globs: server/**/*.ts

## Backend Rules
1. RESTful conventions: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
2. JWT auth middleware on all protected routes
3. Input validation before processing
4. Error format: { error: string }, never expose internals
5. Log errors server-side with context
6. Password hashing with bcryptjs (10 rounds)
7. Passwords never returned in responses
8. CORS with specific origin
9. Route handlers are thin; logic belongs in services (future)
